title.narrative: Strengthening key malaria control interventions for malaria elimination in Chad

description.narrative: Chad - Malaria - United Nations Development Programme - UNDP Chad. This program has the following goals: Help improve the state of health of the country’s population by reducing the human and socio-economic impact of malaria. The objectives of this program are: Successfully complete 80 percent of the malaria control support interventions by the end of 2018.. Cut malaria-related morbidity by 30 percent compared with its 2013 level by the end of 2016, and reduce it by a further 20 percent between 2017 and 2018.
